This paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models for this task, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a new training mechanism, which involves optimizing multiple distributions separately, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
